WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:28.960
It is the first time I come to a Sahaja Yoga seminar, because every time we are different,

00:28.960 --> 00:41.240
the moment is new, the challenge is growing, and we need to move on.

00:41.240 --> 00:50.440
So I have nothing prepared for today.

00:50.440 --> 00:59.000
I just would like to say that when Shri Mataji starts her program, she says,

00:59.000 --> 01:07.960
I bow to all the seekers of truth.

01:07.960 --> 01:23.960
I suppose that I put this in connection with the line from Gandalf in the Lord of the Rings.

01:23.960 --> 01:30.360
Did you hear about the Lord of the Rings?

01:30.360 --> 01:36.360
You see, at some point when everything goes wrong in Middle-earth,

01:36.360 --> 01:45.080
and the power of Mordor and the power of Isengard is too much even for the high elves,

01:45.080 --> 01:57.080
then Mitrandir Gandalf says that help is still to come from ones that we don't expect.

01:57.080 --> 02:04.200
And that help was from the humblest of all the creatures of Middle-earth,

02:04.200 --> 02:19.160
not the warriors, not the wizards, not the elves, the first born, but these little halflings.

02:19.160 --> 02:24.680
So I always have the feeling that someone here in this room,

02:24.680 --> 02:34.280
there is someone who is sitting here, and who is the ring bearer.

02:34.280 --> 02:45.080
There is someone who is sitting here who will escape the temptations which made the higher one fall.

02:45.080 --> 02:54.280
There is someone sitting here who is the seeker of truth and who will carry the transformation

02:54.280 --> 03:02.600
to its appointed hand. And to this seeker, this girl or this boy who is sitting here,

03:02.600 --> 03:09.640
I like to bow.

03:09.640 --> 03:18.200
I like to bow because we need help.

03:18.200 --> 03:24.280
It's quite a battle out there.

03:24.280 --> 03:33.240
It has been very interesting, it has been very challenging, but it hasn't been easy.

03:33.240 --> 03:42.680
Now, it wasn't meant to be easy. And in all the prophetic books,

03:42.680 --> 03:48.920
it was always stated that that would be a difficult time.

03:48.920 --> 03:53.240
Does anyone here have the Bhagavad Gita by any chance?

03:53.240 --> 04:05.000
Those of you who meet and meditate for peace at the same time and the same hour,

04:05.080 --> 04:13.320
do you remember how the Bhagavad Gita started?

04:13.320 --> 04:23.880
Arjuna was seeing in the army of the Kaurava, his friends, his respected and beloved guru,

04:23.880 --> 04:28.760
his cousins. And he sat and he said,

04:28.760 --> 04:33.160
Vishnu, I shall not fight. This is my key to the king. Why should I fight?

04:33.160 --> 04:37.960
Just to gain the kingdom is not worth it. I'd rather die.

04:37.960 --> 04:41.560
And then started the Bhagavad Gita.

04:41.560 --> 04:48.920
In essence, this is a puppet show.

04:48.920 --> 04:57.800
And all in the puppet show, Mr. Saddam, Mr. Bush,

04:57.800 --> 05:03.160
Mr. TrÃ©goire, everyone.

05:06.120 --> 05:09.240
Everybody in this puppet show has some sort of role to play.

05:09.240 --> 05:13.560
With a little luck, they can have a sense for the role. Mostly they don't.

05:13.560 --> 05:21.160
But when there is the time for war, are you going to pray for peace?

05:21.160 --> 05:28.280
Are you at the beginning of the Mahabharata, sit down with Arjuna and say peace?

05:28.280 --> 05:32.840
Are you going to ask Mother for peace?

05:32.840 --> 05:38.280
I prefer peace to war. War is a doom. War is a curse.

05:38.280 --> 05:44.600
War creates boots. Boots generate evil, suffering.

05:44.600 --> 05:49.960
Nobody wishes war. But you are yogis.

05:49.960 --> 05:57.560
So what it is that we pray for as yogis?

05:57.560 --> 06:07.400
Did you get the point? I'm sorry because many people may not know English.

06:07.400 --> 06:13.080
Okay, what we need to pray if we are yogis for?

06:13.080 --> 06:21.720
What we need to pray for is not for war.

06:21.720 --> 06:25.480
Certainly not. Not for peace either.

06:25.480 --> 06:31.480
But for something which is called thy will be done.

06:31.480 --> 06:34.520
It's not the same thing.

06:35.000 --> 06:39.080
And first of all, thy will be done with me.

06:39.080 --> 06:46.520
With each of us. Because the path of growth to Sahaja Yoga is not to achieve something.

06:46.520 --> 06:52.200
It's not to concentrate on something. It's not to bend our little energies

06:52.200 --> 06:58.600
trying to move two lines ahead the cosmic plot.

06:58.600 --> 07:07.160
Our role as yogis is to discover the art of letting the power flow.

07:07.160 --> 07:12.680
Not by straining. Sorry? Oh, okay.

07:12.680 --> 07:19.960
Not by straining. Not by concentrating. By being.

07:19.960 --> 07:29.560
If we are what our mother empowers us to become, then it flows through us.

07:29.560 --> 07:36.440
And then the big advantage compared to concentrating and praying and having projects

07:36.440 --> 07:41.800
is that it does not give us ego.

07:41.800 --> 07:46.200
Because we can be yogis and we carry our ego. Do you know Ravana?

07:46.200 --> 07:54.680
Did you hear about Ravana? Right? Ravana? Anyone? Friend of yours?

07:54.680 --> 08:02.520
Well, for your information, Ravana was a realized soul.

08:02.600 --> 08:06.840
Was a realized soul with some powers because he could even shake Kailash.

08:06.840 --> 08:10.520
Which you can't.

08:10.520 --> 08:19.240
And yet he was Ravana. Why? Because it is possible to walk on the spiritual path

08:19.240 --> 08:24.600
carrying the ego which becomes subtler and subtler and subtler.

08:24.600 --> 08:30.120
And the ego is, I am a Sahaja Yogi and I'm spreading Mother's Kingdom

08:30.200 --> 08:34.280
and I'm doing this and I'm doing that.

08:34.280 --> 08:38.760
There is one mantra which is, I am my own guru.

08:38.760 --> 08:46.120
But some people can put a postscript and write, I am my own fake guru.

08:46.120 --> 08:51.880
It's possible. It's already seen.

08:51.880 --> 08:59.880
It's already practiced. Now for those of us who have this temptation,

09:00.680 --> 09:03.880
we should help such people.

09:06.360 --> 09:09.720
By remembering one thing.

09:12.120 --> 09:14.120
You know,

09:14.120 --> 09:20.120
Ashaduallahu illaaha illa Allah, Ashaduallahu muhmadadah as-Sulluallahu ala.

09:20.120 --> 09:24.280
There is only one God and Muhammad is his prophet.

09:24.280 --> 09:28.840
There is only one deity and there is only one good for us.

09:28.840 --> 09:32.120
And that one is our mother.

09:33.080 --> 09:38.280
So everything which brings us there is helpful.

09:38.280 --> 09:41.000
So is the staircase leading there?

09:41.000 --> 09:44.840
Or is the staircase getting you glued to a step?

09:44.840 --> 09:48.120
Attached to somebody.

09:48.120 --> 09:58.120
Now back to war and peace. It's a nice subject, isn't it?

09:58.120 --> 10:02.120
Nobody has the Bhagavad Gita here, no?

10:02.120 --> 10:08.120
Okay, so do you want to know why there is a war?

10:10.120 --> 10:16.120
Or do you want to know why there might be an apocalypse?

10:16.120 --> 10:26.120
If you do, buy the Bhagavad Gita. I would have spared you the expense if you would have it here.

10:26.120 --> 10:36.120
And read the verse 9-11 of the Bhagavad Gita.

10:36.120 --> 10:42.120
All right? All clear?

10:42.120 --> 10:48.120
9-11, you know what 9-11 is?

10:48.120 --> 10:58.120
Now, if someone has the Gita here, I'll read it for you. If there is no Gita here, you'll have to back home and read it.

10:58.120 --> 11:04.120
That leads to the next point.

11:04.120 --> 11:08.120
You'll see. It's interesting.

11:12.120 --> 11:22.120
The next point is that I don't know anybody who understands Sahaja Yoga.

11:22.120 --> 11:30.120
I don't know anybody who understands who Sri Mataji is.

11:30.120 --> 11:36.120
I don't claim to understand either of them.

11:36.120 --> 11:40.120
I don't claim to understand Sahaja Yoga nor to understand Sri Mataji.

11:41.120 --> 11:49.120
But I see much more clearly now than 30 years ago when I came inside Sahaja Yoga.

11:49.120 --> 11:59.120
And from that clarity, I can only ask you to hang on.

11:59.120 --> 12:12.120
Because you are part, we are part of something which is going to change the face of history.

12:12.120 --> 12:26.120
And even though people would like to put us in a mental hospital for stating it, the truth is that it is so.

12:26.120 --> 12:31.120
Sahaja Yoga is growing.

12:31.120 --> 12:35.120
It doesn't depend on you. It doesn't depend on me.

12:35.120 --> 12:41.120
Any one of you can step out at any time. No one is indispensable. But it is growing.

12:41.120 --> 12:49.120
It is maybe not growing in the area where you live. It is growing in so many different ways.

12:49.120 --> 12:58.120
And again I bow to that unknown boy or girl. I bow to those who will carry this.

12:58.120 --> 13:17.120
Because all of us have a role to play and many of you have still to play yours.

13:17.120 --> 13:29.120
Herbert Heininger, good friend, remember an old seminar we had in Austria a long time back.

13:29.120 --> 13:34.120
I tend to be a bit sentimental when I am among Austrians.

13:34.120 --> 13:42.120
And what we said in those days, yeah because Austrians are nice guys.

13:42.120 --> 13:49.120
Despite the White Mountain and Wallenstein and all this stuff, this is over now.

13:49.120 --> 13:54.120
They are nicer now. They are no longer Catholics.

13:54.120 --> 14:00.120
And one thing that we said then was there are two realities.

14:00.120 --> 14:05.120
There is she and there is we.

14:05.120 --> 14:11.120
And we are the vahana of she.

14:11.120 --> 14:17.120
The extraordinary dimension of Sahaja Yoga is not to get self-realization.

14:17.120 --> 14:20.120
Because other gurus did that before.

14:20.120 --> 14:24.120
Extraordinary dimension of Sahaja Yoga is collective consciousness.

14:24.120 --> 14:33.120
This is why negativity always tries to attack the making of our collective consciousness.

14:33.120 --> 14:38.120
It is going to try to disturb the relationship of friendship between yogis.

14:38.120 --> 14:40.120
For many little reasons.

14:40.120 --> 14:45.120
Going from Moladara up to Sahaja.

14:45.120 --> 14:50.120
It is going to try to prevent people to go in, I shall say.

14:50.120 --> 14:58.120
It is going to try to create jealousies, conflict with the leaders, little groups here, little groups there.

14:58.120 --> 14:59.120
Why?

14:59.120 --> 15:12.120
Because the one thing that the devil fears is the making of the horse.

15:12.120 --> 15:22.120
The white horse of the last rider is the collective consciousness of the realized souls.

15:22.120 --> 15:30.120
If I were the devil I would also do the same. He is a very rational chap.

15:30.120 --> 15:43.120
Now when we are moving towards unity, it helps to understand that none of us can put out much light by ourselves.

15:43.120 --> 15:47.120
It is like the little candle that was just blown away here.

15:47.120 --> 15:53.120
One candle only needs so much, especially in a hall like that.

15:53.120 --> 16:00.120
But if there are hundred candles, you can see where your light and my light ends or starts.

16:00.120 --> 16:09.120
But the total light is simply more effective.

16:09.120 --> 16:22.120
So I think that Shri Mataji did say many times that I am happy or I enjoy when you love each other.

16:22.120 --> 16:28.120
She wrote me once, she wrote me once, she said,

16:28.120 --> 16:34.120
I know you love me very much, but in this way everybody loves me.

16:34.120 --> 16:40.120
They build cathedrals for me. They build mosque for me.

16:40.120 --> 16:49.120
To love Shri Mataji once we start getting an idea of what is going on is not difficult.

16:49.120 --> 16:58.120
So I think where she really relishes is when we start loving each other.

16:58.120 --> 17:01.120
Sometimes difficult, isn't it?

17:01.120 --> 17:07.120
Sahaja Yogi can be such stupid blokes sometimes, don't you think? No?

17:07.120 --> 17:12.120
We need to have protocol of the yogis.

17:12.120 --> 17:18.120
We need to see our strength and forget our weaknesses.

17:18.120 --> 17:28.120
Like mother, when I came to her there was a big, big, big lump of mud and a diamond, she said,

17:28.120 --> 17:34.120
I wouldn't have a clue of course, but a diamond under the mud. I wouldn't see that.

17:34.120 --> 17:38.120
Well, what she did, she chose to look at the diamond and not at the mud.

17:38.120 --> 17:42.120
And I think that was very helpful for me.

17:42.120 --> 17:47.120
That she could have legitimately looked at the mud because it was there too.

17:47.120 --> 17:54.120
So the problem is not to see reality, the problem is to create reality.

17:54.120 --> 18:02.120
To have the vision of that reality that we want to make happen.

18:03.120 --> 18:13.120
And that we can start by understanding how the we is important.

18:13.120 --> 18:16.120
The we is the only protection against the little I.

18:16.120 --> 18:19.120
The big I is the self, so the big I is the right.

18:19.120 --> 18:22.120
The little I is the ego and the ego is a clever chap.

18:22.120 --> 18:27.120
You think that you push him through the door and it comes back from the window.

18:27.120 --> 18:31.120
No, not easy.

18:31.120 --> 18:40.120
When we are together, we are completely protected from that.

18:40.120 --> 18:47.120
So I was requested to speak briefly. I think I will stop here.

18:50.120 --> 18:57.120
I think the idea of the organizers, a privilege that I don't share, I'm here just to guest,

18:57.120 --> 19:07.120
is to ask you to ask any question whatsoever which is not completely foolish.

19:07.120 --> 19:15.120
And in any language that you want because people can translate.

19:15.120 --> 19:25.120
And then some friends here sitting on a bench or some of you or whatever would choose to answer.

19:26.120 --> 19:31.120
Is this alright? Should we go that way?

19:34.120 --> 19:37.120
So you see even in the United Nations one might respect time.

19:37.120 --> 19:39.120
Thank you very much.

19:55.120 --> 19:59.120
Get up. Get up please.

20:01.120 --> 20:07.120
I remember just now that Gregor has said,

20:07.120 --> 20:19.120
someone here in the room, some boy or girl has the ring and that we need help.

20:19.120 --> 20:29.120
So I think if you come forward with questions, it will help. Thank you.

20:29.120 --> 20:52.120
And if I may add, we all know it's not easy because also I'm sitting here and the pulse is a little faster than normal.

20:52.120 --> 21:02.120
And everyone who has a question in his heart and probably considers to come forward, all to the pulse is rising up.

21:02.120 --> 21:11.120
But I can tell you how the pulse rate is if you come here.

21:22.120 --> 21:26.120
Come here.

21:41.120 --> 21:50.120
I have a question that came up very often the last few months actually while we had public programs, doing programs.

21:50.120 --> 21:58.120
And I realized one of the last weeks that the way we explain raising Kundalini to new people is different.

21:58.120 --> 22:00.120
So that's one of my questions.

22:00.120 --> 22:14.120
It's exactly the way a lot of us are used to is to raise the Kundalini to a knot and then the second time do two knots.

22:14.120 --> 22:20.120
It's just a tiny little question but in fact it's explained differently.

22:20.120 --> 22:24.120
So I wondered what you're doing.

22:45.120 --> 22:50.120
The pulse rate. I checked the pulse rate.

22:50.120 --> 22:52.120
There is nothing.

22:58.120 --> 23:07.120
If I could remember, there is one video which Mataji, where she is showing it.

23:07.120 --> 23:12.120
I remember it well, where you see it clearly shown.

23:12.120 --> 23:20.120
Always do it not thinking of left channel, right channel, whatever might be also thought about.

23:20.120 --> 23:24.120
And just to do it, try it.

23:24.120 --> 23:31.120
What I remember it was first time one knot, second time two knots, third time three knots.

23:31.120 --> 23:34.120
And then the burn down.

23:34.120 --> 23:39.120
This is what I remember. If somebody remembers different, please.

23:39.120 --> 23:45.120
Maybe there is something to add.

23:45.120 --> 23:48.120
I think the process is really two processes.

23:48.120 --> 23:53.120
One is raising the Kundalini and the other one is tying it up.

23:53.120 --> 24:01.120
I have very often had the privilege of witnessing Shri Mataji working on people,

24:01.120 --> 24:05.120
on new people or old people or sick people or whatsoever.

24:05.120 --> 24:10.120
And in the end she would always say to us, now tie him up.

24:10.120 --> 24:17.120
Alright, so it is really the one thing is rising the Kundalini

24:17.120 --> 24:23.120
and the other thing is tying the Kundalini up in the sense of connecting the individual to the Divine

24:23.120 --> 24:29.120
and establishing that connection which is done by the three knots.

24:29.120 --> 24:37.120
And one should be very, very clear about the fact that this is not a symbolic thing.

24:37.120 --> 24:41.120
We are not doing this as a symbolic process,

24:41.120 --> 24:45.120
nor are we doing the knots as a symbol,

24:45.120 --> 24:52.120
which many people sometimes like to say to new people because they themselves feel a bit strange about it.

24:52.120 --> 24:59.120
But no, in fact, it is an actual process which is done and we cannot see what we are doing,

24:59.120 --> 25:03.120
but we can feel what's happening when we have done it.

25:03.120 --> 25:10.120
So it is very important to remember it is an actual process

25:10.120 --> 25:15.120
which has an actual meaning, it has an actual effect

25:15.120 --> 25:20.120
and it is divided in two things which is rising the Kundalini and tying it up.

25:20.120 --> 25:24.120
Thank you. Doesn't that answer the question?

25:24.120 --> 25:27.120
May I ask a question?

25:27.120 --> 25:29.120
There is a question.

25:29.120 --> 25:31.120
Good job.

25:31.120 --> 25:33.120
Okay.

25:33.120 --> 25:35.120
There is also one question.

25:35.120 --> 25:40.120
When we give realization, many people ask,

25:40.120 --> 25:46.120
what do you think about the USA and Iraq, about the war which is going to come?

25:46.120 --> 25:50.120
And actually, we don't really know.

25:50.120 --> 25:55.120
Shri Mataji says that Bush is a nice person, but is he nice because he is really nice

25:55.120 --> 26:02.120
or is it just nice because he is going to expose all the wrong things going on?

26:02.120 --> 26:09.120
So what about you say in Iraq about the war?

26:09.120 --> 26:13.120
Take that one. That's yours.

26:13.120 --> 26:15.120
Five minutes.

26:15.120 --> 26:17.120
Five minutes?

26:17.120 --> 26:21.120
Three minutes.

26:21.120 --> 26:23.120
You all have been generous.

26:23.120 --> 26:33.120
I would like to suggest this.

26:33.120 --> 26:35.120
Well, I'll go back to a little anecdote.

26:35.120 --> 26:38.120
I visited Shri Mataji during the Gulf War.

26:38.120 --> 26:42.120
During the Gulf War, she told me I am protecting the American army.

26:42.120 --> 26:47.120
Two hours later, I was in the plane leaving Delhi and I opened the Newsweek

26:47.120 --> 26:55.120
and I read an article where a corporal who was on a Humvee vehicle with three other Marines

26:55.120 --> 26:58.120
got hit by a mortar.

26:58.120 --> 27:01.120
The vehicle got hit by a mortar from the Iraqis.

27:01.120 --> 27:08.120
So the ship or the Humvee went 20 meters in the air and was completely destroyed.

27:08.120 --> 27:12.120
All the four people were alive and in the Newsweek it was written,

27:12.120 --> 27:15.120
the corporal was saying that was nothing short of a complete miracle.

27:15.120 --> 27:19.120
I read this two hours after mother told me I protect the American army.

27:19.120 --> 27:21.120
So this is the first war.

27:21.120 --> 27:29.120
Now, I did ask Shri Mataji about Bush because I felt that the policies of Bush were about everything

27:29.120 --> 27:37.120
that I found abominable in the beginning with the Kyoto Protocol, with the Civil Court of Justice,

27:37.120 --> 27:39.120
so many aspects of his policy.

27:39.120 --> 27:50.120
But Shri Mataji did confirm very clearly that she sees qualities of Bush

27:50.120 --> 27:56.120
and what I understand is that Bush is not like many European intellectuals,

27:56.120 --> 27:58.120
a constructed personality.

27:58.120 --> 28:03.120
He is very spontaneous and in a sense he is very innocent.

28:03.120 --> 28:08.120
It is very difficult for Western intellectuals to go along with a type like that

28:08.120 --> 28:15.120
because he is in black and white and good and evil and intellectual like to discuss grey shades.

28:15.120 --> 28:17.120
He is not at all like that.

28:17.120 --> 28:23.120
So I think that it is true that Shri Mataji does support his action

28:23.120 --> 28:30.120
and that she was very clearly saying that she can work through him.

28:30.120 --> 28:35.120
Now when Shri Mataji said that she can work through him, no one understand what she means,

28:35.120 --> 28:39.120
neither I, again, because we don't know what the purpose is.

28:39.120 --> 28:46.120
As far as Saddam Hussein is concerned, I think that was quite clear from the first Gulf War

28:46.120 --> 28:48.120
that he is a rakshasa.

28:48.120 --> 28:55.120
So that's what I can say.

28:55.120 --> 28:59.120
I don't ask you to vote left or to vote right.

28:59.120 --> 29:01.120
I don't ask you to vote for Bush.

29:01.120 --> 29:06.120
I am just saying there is a game out there which is beyond us and as Sahaja Yogi,

29:06.120 --> 29:10.120
we can sort of watch and see what's happening.

29:10.120 --> 29:12.120
I think it is completely out of our hands.

29:12.120 --> 29:14.120
Anyways, what else to do?

29:14.120 --> 29:22.120
Eat popcorn in the movie hall. That's it.

29:22.120 --> 29:26.120
What do you say to new people has nothing to do with Sahaja Yoga?

29:26.120 --> 29:30.120
Politics is one thing, Sahaja Yoga is completely different.

29:30.120 --> 29:34.120
If people don't like Bush, it's fine.

29:34.120 --> 29:37.120
If you don't like Bush, don't like Bush.

29:37.120 --> 29:40.120
You don't need to like him because you are a yogi.

29:40.120 --> 29:43.120
I didn't like his environmental policies at all.

29:43.120 --> 29:45.120
It has nothing to do with Sahaja.

29:45.120 --> 29:51.120
If you ask me what mother said about Bush, I try to give you a feedback because I talk directly about it.

29:51.120 --> 29:53.120
So this is not his say.

29:53.120 --> 29:56.120
It's something that I know.

29:56.120 --> 30:00.120
I had this discussion already when he was competing with Al Gore.

30:00.120 --> 30:05.120
In my view, Al Gore, the democratic challenger, had much better policies.

30:05.120 --> 30:09.120
Al Gore is an extremely mental person and when people are very cerebral,

30:09.120 --> 30:13.120
the inspiration from their unconscious don't come.

30:13.120 --> 30:17.120
I'm not saying that mother is a mother.

30:17.120 --> 30:19.120
She doesn't like war at all.

30:19.120 --> 30:27.120
Maybe she sees that there are 300 vectors with microbiological dirty bombs stored somewhere.

30:27.120 --> 30:29.120
What do I know?

30:29.120 --> 30:30.120
What do I know?

30:30.120 --> 30:32.120
So everybody says the war is a horrible thing.

30:32.120 --> 30:37.120
